snippet.textDisplay:
At the door to what? The door at the center of the domed earth. It’s near the breaking point where the Earth’s pressure with be released. The blacked out sun shown in the video is the “black hole sun.” At one point in the video it shows rocks and stuff getting sucked up into it. It goes deeper and the channel “Jaydreamerz” talks about this stuff. The white robed people are heavenly creatures of wisdom. The way everything on earth is destroyed at the end is the result of this “apocalypse” (a wasteland earth). The beautiful place shown at the end is a new place/planet where the elite plan on going when this event happens.

I think Julian is saying the thing will happen after he dies or that he’s going to have to stay behind for some reason.

snippet.textDisplay:
OK, read some great interpretatons, but here is mine. Dont know if its because I work on that subject, but to me, the song depicts the point of view of a child migrant, knocking at the door of an over developed country, lets say the US, and getting no response. Then interiorizing (dont know how to write that word) that rejection and feeling ugly and undeserving. Aftwr that its all a spiral, its like you are making the trip with him, listening to his doubts, am I going to make it?.. Oh, and that fat guy that is like the comander of the ship reminds me of Trump, orange and hollow eyed...

And on top of this, I spot another subject, deeply related, witch is climate change, a subject that the strokes have somewhat tackled before , for example, in heart in a cage, "the sun will be shinning and my children will burn". I spot this in the video more than the lyrics, in the eclipse, in the astronaut looking back at earth, or in the rabbit that mutates and hurts the other one, like nature turning against itself. (the face of the rabbit when he gets scratched is just to sad...)

What a great song, what a great band. And the actual sound, like a goth anthem remixed in the 80s. Pure cyber punk. Just love it. Its a New versión of the strokes and Thats so cool, they have changed so much over the years and some how they still manage to have something unique that when you hear it you say, yes, its them. Fucking awsome.

When you make a music video about cancer mixed with the 1980s and somehow no one noticed nearly half of that stuff is back when trying to find a cure for Cancer is way harder compared to the modern 2020s.


Chemotherapy kills more people than help them sadly and it sadly still does. It could also be a message that there is a cure for cancer at the end of the video when we enter the next world but the powers that be want to prevent that from happening. This is the same powers that be claimed that Cannabis aka marijuana harmed kids and or cause people to go insane when it is the opposite.


The moral of the story is that the 1980s had way lot of people die of cancer compared to nowadays where even with better understanding and tech that can stop it from spreading but it will cost lots of money just to stop it.
